     <h2>Letter To A Loved One</h2>
     <hr style=" border: solid 1px #fff; margin:10px auto 10px auto;" />
<p>Hey,</p> 

<p>You didn't expect this, huh? I didn't either.</p> 
<p>I know I hardly ever talk about you, instead, I keep you in between the lines of those poems that are locked up in my journal, I don't let anyone read, yet I still keep holding onto the threads of your flesh. That's what I say at least, when in fact, somehow those strings have made their way around my fingers and I'm too afraid to pull them out and let you go. </p>

<p>You're not happy, how can you be? When I've tied you up in a fortress filled with the terrors, that come to me at times when I board the metro too late and with those thoughts that force my tongue to keep reciting those tables, I learnt in my childhood, of 12s, 13s and 14s, only to push those thoughts away. </p>

<p>Then there's this thing that you've always dreaded yet it's true, it's the fact that I can't let you out, that I can't save you.</p>

<p>I can't save you, even when some years ago you saved me when you didn't have to and even though I begged you not to, you did.</p> 

<p>So all I've come to say is;</p>
<p>I'm sorry,</p>

<p>I'm sorry that you've to carry the weight that belongs to me,</p>

<p>I'm sorry that you've to drink down the memories of everyone who were led in by me,</p>

<p>And the most I'm sorry for is those dead flowers I keep handing back to you while you keep blooming fresh ones for me. </p>

                        <p>- to the girl, I was before.</p> 
